## HEAVY UPRIGHT ROWS

PURPOSE OF EXERCISE: A heavy cheating movement
for advanced bodybuilders to strengthen the entire
shoulder girdle and upper back.

EXECUTION: (1) Choose a heavy barbell and grasp it
with an overhand grip, hands about 12 inches apart.
Let the bar hang down at arm's length in front of
you. (2) Lift the bar straight up to a point just below
your chin, allowing yourself to choat by swaying
with the back, pushing with the legs, and even help-
ing with the calves. As you lift, keep your elbows out
and up higher than the bar. Then lower the bar back
to the starting position. Remember, this is a power
movement in which cheating plays a vital part. This
makes Heavy Upright Rows quite a different exer-
