Many gyms are equipped with a variety
of specialized rowing machines. Some
duplicate the effect of Seated Rows,
while others allow you to do a rowing
motion by pushing back with the elbows
and not involving the contraction of the
biceps. Each of these hits the back a lit-
tle differently, and all are useful devices
to include occasionally in your workouts
to provide variety and to surprise the
muscles.


