## DEADLIFTS

PURPOSE OF EXERCISE: To work the
lower back. Deadlifts are an overall
power exercise that involves more
muscles than any other exercise in
your routine, including the lower
back, upper back, and trapezius
muscles, the buttocks, and the legs.
A strong lower back is especially
important when doing movements
like Bent-Over Rows and T-Bar
Rows, which put a lot of strain on
this area.

EXECUTION: (1) Place a barbell on
the floor in front of you. Bend your
knees, lean forward, and grasp the
