from strain. If you curve your back
you risk injury. (2) Begin the lift by
driving with the legs. Straighten up
until you are standing upright, then
throw the chest out and shoulders
back as if coming to attention. To
lower the weight, bend the knees,
lean forward from the waist, and
touch the weight to the floor before
beginning your next repetition.

