# TRAINING THE ABDOMINALS

Strong abdominals are essential to maximizing performance in almost all
sports. In bodybuilding, the abdominals play an extremely important role
when it comes to the visible impression your physique makes on an ob-
server. The abs are, in fact, the visual center of the body. If you superim-
pose an X on the body with the terminal points being the shoulders and
the feet, the two lines cross at the abdominals, and this is where the eyes
are inevitably drawn. Men carry a disproportionate number of fat cells in
the abdominal area compared to women (who can often be relatively fat
and still have abs showing), so well-defined abs are one sign of being in top
condition-lean, hard, and strong.

A bodybuilder is likely to score points in a contest if he has wide shoul-
ders and flaring lats that taper down to a firm, narrow waist. A small waist

