Many people don't realize it, but the posedown as we know it today
came about because of a battle between Sergio Oliva and me at the 1970
Olympia in Columbus. Until that time the judges brought out the finalists
and simply asked them to do certain set poses for direct comparison. That
evening we were doing a double-biceps shot-one of my best poses-and

