The important thing to remember is that improvisation requires an
absolute command of each pose, an ability to move from one to another
smoothly and gracefully. The only way to acquire this kind of skill-so that
you appear just as competent and graceful during the posedown as you do
performing your own routine-is by hard and constant practice.

Always remember the reason for the posedown-it's your chance to
garner a few extra and maybe essential points. The judges are looking for
the winner, the bodybuilder to whom they will each give a final placing, so
it is important to act like a winner, to stand there confidently with a smile
on your face, as if the whole thing was a piece of cake. The idea of com-
petition, after all, is to try to win.

